                  <msItem>
                     <p> ROUSHAM and BARTON. <persName>
                           <forename>Richard</forename> 
                           <surname>Folioth</surname> of <placeName role="person" key="place_109459">Rolesham</placeName>
                        </persName> 
               confirms to the <orgName key="org_109067">church and canons of St. Mary, Oseney</orgName>, the donation and concession which
               <persName>
                           <forename>Henry</forename> de <surname>Sandon</surname>, clerk</persName>, made to
               them by his charter of the whole of the land which he held of the fee of the said
               Richard in <placeName key="place_109292">Barthon</placeName> and in <placeName key="place_109459">Rolesham</placeName>, paying annually for the land 
               of Barthon 4d., and for scutage 18d., and for the land of Rolesham one pound of cummin. For this grant
               the said canons gave 4 1/2 marks of silver. 
               (<origDate notBefore="1230" notAfter="1240" precision="low">c. 1230-40</origDate>.) 
               . </p>
